The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 VSP to hire consultant

 OUR CORRESPONDENT 

 Hyderabad, April 7: The Vishakpatnam Steel Plant (VSP) plans to appoint an international consulting firm to offer advice on buying iron ore and acquiring coking coal mines, according to chairman Y. Shiv Sagar Rao . The consultant would also help VSP find new markets for its products.

 VSP has recorded an all-time high turnover of Rs 8,469 crore and profit of Rs 1,200 crore in 2005-06.VSP operated at 120 per cent capacity and produced 4.152 million tonnes (mt) of hot metal, 3.603 mt of liquid steel and 3.236 mt of saleable steel. We sold 9.27 lakh tonnes of value added steel and 44,012 tonnes of spring steel during the year, Shiv Sagar said. 




